properties.name: Battery Park Chambers Street Meetup
properties.description: When we say Battery Park this is what we mean.  Always meet up at the end of Chambers street here when there is a jam announced for battery.  Security can be tight or lax, it varies.

properties.name: Pace University
properties.description: CURRENTLY UNDER CONSTRUCTIONRight outside the spot you will see squares and ledges.  This is the meetup spot for Pace University trainings

properties.name: Columbus Park South
properties.description: This area of the park has a bar setup and a lot of ledges when the sprinklers aren't turned on.

properties.name: Columbus Park North
properties.description: this back area of the park has more walls and gates for vaults

properties.name: BOK LEI PO TRADING INC (Buy Fieyues Here)
properties.description:
$18 for white and $20 for black

http://store.bokleipo.com/index.php?

properties.name: Scoops 1
properties.description: This is the famous scoops spot in the lower east side.  Don't make too much noise or be a nuisance since the people here already like us.  Don't ruin that.  Be respectful.

properties.name: Scoops 2
properties.description: Once again, don't make it hot.  Have fun, train hard, be respectful

properties.name: Tompkins Square Park Bars
properties.description: These are one of the only bar playgrounds still around in NYC.  Come train on the yellow, blue or red setups.  Easiest way to get here is walk to the corner of Ave B and East 10th street and you'll see the bars

properties.name: NYC Department of Parks & Recreation: Hamilton Fish Park
properties.description: When we say HAMFISH this is where we mean.  Usually the next spot after a Scoops meetup

properties.name: Fort Tryon Park
properties.description: When you get to 190th street make sure you walk ALL the way down St.Michels Promenade so you can see the big stone walls we all use to train on, pictured above.
*CURRENTLY UNDER CONSTRUCTION*We call it 351 cause its on East 35th street and 1st avenue.  You cant miss it bunch of beige walls and open to the public signs on the walls.

properties.name: Blackwell Playground
properties.description: First meetup spot of the Roosevelt Island route.  Can't miss the giant stone circles and mulch play area.  Right next to the basketball courts

properties.name: Adventure Playground
properties.description: One of the best playground spots in Central Park.  Don't go in big groups and avoid during afterschool hours cause it gets crowded.  Two main parks here to hit.  One is the above and the other is right next to it with a bunch of circles.  You can't miss it.  Right by Tavern on the Green Restuarant

properties.name: Heckscher Playground
properties.description: Another sanctuary spot in NYC.  Everyone in the community knows about this place.  You can usually find other parkour people by the picnic tables around the wooden fence by the Giant Rock to the LEFT of the playground area.  Be mindful of children.  Better to go here in the fall and winter

properties.name: Sanctuary Jam Meetup Spot
properties.description: We meet here for the sanctuary jams before walking to the actual spot inside Riverside.  If you come here and are late you might as well just walk to Sanctuary

properties.name: SANCTUARY
properties.description: This spot has red awnings and wooden picnic tables and benches.  Surrounded by a beautiful view of the hudson and Jersey

properties.name: Bethesda Fountain
properties.description: Cool climbing and traversing challenges here.  A few jumps here and there, and public bathrooms.  Be mindful of the public eye.

properties.name: Ancient playground
properties.description: Another awesome playground with some great architecture for training!  Be wary of kids and non-approving parents though!

properties.name: Frederick Douglass Sculpture and Water Wall
properties.description: Great spot for strides and precisions.  Longer lines and good challenges here.  Check the corners cause skaters sometimes wax the edges up.

properties.name: Columbia University Department of Biomedical Engineering
properties.description: This is the first spot we usually start at during Columbia Jams.  The spot has small steps and multiple black railings.

properties.name: Riverbank State Park Tennis Courts
properties.description: This whole park is great.  Enter on the 137th street entrance and when you walk in you'll see a playground and walls.  That the first spot we always meet at when we do  a RIVERBANK jam.  ABOVE:  The meetup spot would be in the lower right hand corner

properties.name: Bryant Park Café
properties.description: A few big jumps to hit here but only in the warm weather.  Security is tight so stay in a small group.  You could either be here for a while or you can get kicked in 10 minutes

properties.name: New York Vietnam Veterans Memorial Plaza
properties.description: Fun spot when its dry.  Lots of marble here.  Security could be tight too.  Depends on the time and day.

properties.name: Water Street Courtyard
properties.description: Small spot here with some good height challenges.  Security is tight so heads up

properties.name: Sunshine Playground
properties.description: Nice quiet place inside the city to train rail stuff.  Also walking distance from another awesome secret spot inside the housing projects.

properties.name: Semi-Circle
properties.description: This spot is inside the housing projects but you can't miss it.  It's a light blue wall circled around another light blue platform.  Surrounded by benches and chess tables.  Stay out of the grass though

properties.name: Asser Levy Recreation Center
properties.description: Right outside the Rec center there is a public workout park that has benches and rails you can train on.  Really close walk to the 351 spot

properties.name: Ferry Terminal to Manhattan
properties.description: Meet up here to leave Staten Island after jams are over and get back into Manhattan

properties.name: Meet up for Staten Island Ferry
properties.description: Meetup point before jams in Staten Island.  IF you miss the meetup just take the ferry across and link up with the group then.

properties.name: Dollar Pizza
properties.description: Just like it says.  $1 a slice.

properties.name: 2 Bros Pizza
properties.description: $1 a slice.  Close to Thompkins Square Park.

properties.name: Highline Playground
properties.description: This is a small but pretty awesome spot.  Good for strides and precisions.  Awesome backdrop for videos.  Watch out for security cause this is a childrens playground.

properties.name: Pepsi Sign
properties.description: Good place to start the LIC spot route.  Some walls and awesome backdrop for filming.

properties.name: Pier Spot
properties.description: This area has a few more ledges and varied areas to train and is right next to the turf field for acro training!

properties.name: Train Tracks
properties.description: This spot is in between a dog park and a child playground with old train tracks in between perfect for precision training.

properties.name: Brooklyn Banks Skatepark
properties.description: This spot was in the videogame Tony Hawk Pro Skater 2.  Awesome old NYC spot with graffiti, rails, dirty ledges, and skaters.  One of the coolest and chillest spots in the city

properties.name: LES Skatepark
properties.description: They film a lot of  movie and tv show scenes here so maybe you'll get lucky and get discovered.  Awesome skate park and surrounding areas for training.

properties.name: STRIDE
properties.description: This spot is way up in the Bronx but so nice for training.  Many different things to work here.  Don't go by yourself and don't be loud.

properties.name: Lou Gehrig Plaza
properties.description: One of the first meetup spots for Bronx Jams.  Right across the street from the courthouses, skaters also use this spot so check for wax on edges

properties.name: Herbert Von King Park
properties.description: Another sleeper spot in deep Brooklyn.  Go to the area where the bathrooms are and thats the best place to meetup and start the jammage right by the rainbow wall and stage

properties.name: Grace Havenwaller Learning Center
properties.description: Another one of the legit best spots in the city.  Security is low and level of jumps range from beginner to advanced all in one spot.

properties.name: Brooklyn Bridge Park - Pier 2
properties.description: Cool spot with a sick backdrop for photos.  Great turf fields for acro training and scattered pk spots around.  Security level is medium here

properties.name: Brooklyn Zoo NY
properties.description: NYC's premier Parkour/Freerunning Indoor Gym.  Must visit at least once.  2nd floor is great.

properties.name: Playground For All Children
properties.description: LITERALLY A HIDDEN GEM.  ONE OF THE MOST AMAZING SPOTS IN QUEENS.  RIGHT BY THE HALL OF SCIENCE IN FLUSHING MEADOW PARK.  WATCH OUT FOR KIDS!!!

properties.name: Hoffman Park
properties.description: Some challenges here.  Right across the street from QCM.  Quite area good for small groups and exploring less the ideal public places.

properties.name: Directions from Brooklyn Banks Skatepark to Brooklyn Banks Skatepark
